The Junior Springboks will face England in the semifinals of the Junior World Championship after going down 46-29 to hosts France and finishing second in Pool C. JOHANNESBURG- The Junior Springboks will face England in the semifinals of the World Rugby U20 Championship after going down 46-29 to hosts France and finishing second in Pool C. The hosts dominated the first half to take a commanding 36-7 lead at half-time. The Junior Boks then clawed their way back into the game but the French under-20’s held off their onslaught. Chean Roux’s Baby Boks will now face an unbeaten England side in the last four of the tournament on 12 June, while France will take on the Baby All Blacks in the second semifinal on the same day. 